    "comment": "Rationale: Prior knowledge (PMID:12176979): IMPA1 (myo-inositol monophosphatase, IMPase) is an enzyme of the inositol-1,4,5-trisphosphate signaling cascade that is activated by the Ca2+-binding protein calbindin D28k (CB).\n\nUsing FRAP technique the paper shows that the CB interacts with IMPase in dendritic spines of cerebellar Purkinje, implying that both proteins localise there.\n\n09/10/2017 Pim\n- In in order to track CB translocaltion. this protein is of rat species (\"Rat recombinant CB expressed ...\").. Experimental description: CB protein is of rat species (\"Rat recombinant CB expressed ...\").",
